The Securities Industry Associationsaid it strongly supports the decision yesterday by the SenateBanking Committee to freeze the entry by commerical banks intonon-banking businesses such as the underwriting of commericalpaper.    "This committee vote is not only a prudent and thoughtfulapproach to review of the Glass-Steagall Act, but a strong andneeded message from the Senate that it is the responsibility ofCongress to review, and if necessary, amend the nation'sbanking laws," the association said in a statement. Reuter&#3;